  "prompt": "How should I prepare for physics NEET 2017 and from where do I start ?",
  "response": "To prepare for NEET 2017 Physics, here's a structured approach:\n\n1. Study Material:\n- NCERT Physics textbooks (Class 11 and 12)\n- Coaching institute study materials\n- Reference books like HC Verma, DC Pandey\n- Objective physics books by Cengage/MTG\n\n2. Preparation Strategy:\n- Start with NCERT thoroughly\n- Understand concepts, not just memorize\n- Practice numerical problems\n- Focus on important topics with high weightage\n\n3. Important Topics:\n- Mechanics\n- Electromagnetism\n- Optics\n- Modern Physics\n- Thermodynamics\n\n4. Preparation Timeline:\n- 6-8 months before exam: Comprehensive study\n- 3-4 months before: Revision\n- Last 1-2 months: Mock tests and previous years' papers\n\n5. Daily Routine:\n- 4-6 hours dedicated study\n- Solve at least 50 problems daily\n- Regular revision\n- Mock tests on weekends\n\n6. Resources:\n- Online video lectures\n- Coaching center modules\n- Previous years' question papers\n- Online test series\n\n7. Tips:\n- Make concise notes\n- Solve numericals systematically\n- Time management\n- Stay confident and calm\n\nRecommended starting point: NCERT Physics textbooks and fundamental concepts.",
